; Test case from issue #995
; Using --group-by commodity with -V (market valuation) caused a segfault
; because changed_value_posts::clear() called create_accounts() before
; item_handler<post_t>::clear(), leaving the <Revalued> account pointer
; dangling when the next group tried to use it.
;
; Also tests the @@ (total lot cost) annotation which was present in the
; original report.

P 2011/10/01 VTSMX $38.50

2011/10/02 Backdoor Roth, fix investment
    Assets:Investments:Roth IRA:VTSMX  127.996 VTSMX @@ $5500.00
    Assets:Investments:Roth IRA

2011/10/03 Another purchase
    Assets:Investments:Roth IRA:VTSMX  10.000 VTSMX @ $38.50
    Assets:Investments:Roth IRA

test reg --group-by commodity -V
$
11-Oct-02 Backdoor Roth, fix .. As:Investment:Roth IRA    $-5500.00    $-5500.00
11-Oct-03 Another purchase      As:Investment:Roth IRA     $-385.00    $-5885.00

VTSMX
11-Oct-02 Backdoor Roth, fix .. As:Inves:Roth IR:VTSMX     $5500.00     $5500.00
11-Oct-03 Commodities revalued  <Revalued>                 $-572.15     $4927.85
11-Oct-03 Another purchase      As:Inves:Roth IR:VTSMX      $385.00     $5312.85
end test
